You accepted a bounty notice asking you to reduce the number of spiders in Jalkhûl. It can be found to the south-east of Jadambor.

You inform Zûfan about the completed bounty.

'That is the best news I have heard all day. I will let the people here know that the caves to the south will be a bit safer for now. My thanks adventurer.

'Be sure to check the board for more requests, we need all the help we can get down here.'

Defeat spiders to help make the area safer
A bounty has been posted with a request to go to Jalkhûl in the south and cull the number of spiders in the area.
Reach Jalkhûl to the south-east of Jadambor

The bounty notice reads:

We need someone to do something about the spiders that have taken over the southern passage through Dil-irmíz.

They have overrun Jalkhûl and now that area is not open to anyone, guard and smuggler alike. Zûfan here in Jadambor has offered a reward for anyone who can help us thin their numbers.

They can be dangerous. You may want to bring some companions.
That is the best news I have heard all day
